// docs/spec/en/05-unions-and-packed-layout.md §9.4(4): "the number of
// elements in the array ... shall be greater than zero. A program that
// violates ... [this] requirement is ill-formed." Before this feature,
// the parser only ever accepted a bare integer-literal token and never
// checked its value against zero, so `char zero_bound[0];` was silently
// accepted; this must now be a clean, rejected diagnostic.
int main() {
    char zero_bound[0];
    zero_bound[0] = 'a';
    return 0;
}
